Azimio la Umoja presidential candidate Raila Odinga and his running mate Martha Karua led the Coalition's campaigns in the Maa region. Sunday was Raila's second day in Narok County where he pitched tents to hunt for votes. A mega final rally was held in Ole Ntimama stadium where a mammoth crowd turned up to welcome them. Present were Kitui Governor Charity Ngilu, Narok senator Ledama Ole Kina, Former Gatanga MP Peter Kenneth, and Suna East MP Junet Mohammed among other Azimio allies.